      <div class="body entry-content"><div class="sqs-layout sqs-grid-12 columns-12" data-type="item" id="item-51f73431e4b03d20c9b31c84"><div class="row sqs-row"><div class="col sqs-col-12 span-12"><div class="sqs-block html-block" data-block-json="&#123;&quot;html&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;Beautiful video on the &lt;a href=\&quot;http://seriouspony.com/about/\&quot;&gt;about page of Kathy Sierra's new blog&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;100 years after horses were declared \&quot;obsolete\&quot;, the recreational horse industry in the United States alone is $40billion. Yes, that's with a \&quot;b\&quot;. Sometimes a technological replacement reveals a deeper underlying value. From printed books to vinyl records, not&amp;nbsp;everything&amp;nbsp;rendered obsolete vanishes.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;wysiwyg&quot;:&#123;&quot;html&quot;:&quot;&lt;blockquote&gt;Not all that technology replaces is obsolete&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;100 years after horses were declared \&quot;obsolete\&quot;, the recreational horse industry in the United States alone is $40billion. Yes, that's with a \&quot;b\&quot;. Sometimes a technological replacement reveals a deeper underlying value. From printed books to vinyl records, not\u00A0everything\u00A0rendered obsolete vanishes.\u00A0&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&quot;&#125;&#125;" data-block-type="2" id="block-79cf041dd3fa5a1fe3b6"><div class="sqs-block-content"><p>Beautiful video on the <a href="http://seriouspony.com/about/">about page of Kathy Sierra's new blog</a>:<br></p><p></p><p></p><blockquote>100 years after horses were declared "obsolete", the recreational horse industry in the United States alone is $40billion. Yes, that's with a "b". Sometimes a technological replacement reveals a deeper underlying value. From printed books to vinyl records, not&nbsp;everything&nbsp;rendered obsolete vanishes.</blockquote><p></p></div></div></div></div><div class="row sqs-row"><div class="col sqs-col-12 span-12"><div class="sqs-block video-block" data-block-json="&#123;&quot;overlay&quot;:true,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://youtu.be/oO9gU3pz7dI&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;100 years after the automobile, and we're still riding.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Horses: this is why&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:480,&quot;thumbnail_width&quot;:480,&quot;width&quot;:854,&quot;html&quot;:&quot;&lt;iframe width=\&quot;854\&quot; height=\&quot;480\&quot; src=\&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/oO9gU3pz7dI?feature=oembed&amp;amp;wmode=opaque&amp;amp;enablejsapi=1\&quot; frameborder=\&quot;0\&quot; allowfullscreen=\&quot;\&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&quot;,&quot;version&quot;:&quot;1.0&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;video&quot;,&quot;thumbnail_height&quot;:360,&quot;authorName&quot;:&quot;Kathy Sierra&quot;,&quot;authorUrl&quot;:&quot;http://www.youtube.com/user/KathySierraVideos&quot;,&quot;providerName&quot;:&quot;YouTube&quot;,&quot;providerUrl&quot;:&quot;http://www.youtube.com/&quot;,&quot;thumbnailUrl&quot;:&quot;http://i1.ytimg.com/vi/oO9gU3pz7dI/hqdefault.jpg&quot;,&quot;resolvedBy&quot;:&quot;youtube&quot;,&quot;resolveObject&quot;:&quot;Video&quot;,&quot;resolved&quot;:true&#125;" data-block-type="32" id="block-1277d673600fc62e3439"><div class="sqs-block-content"><div class="intrinsic" style="max-width:100%"><div class="embed-block-wrapper" style="padding-bottom:56.20609%;"><div class="sqs-video-wrapper" data-html="&lt;iframe width=&quot;854&quot; height=&quot;480&quot; src=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/oO9gU3pz7dI?feature=oembed&amp;wmode=opaque&amp;enablejsapi=1&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;" data-provider-name="YouTube"><div class="sqs-video-overlay" style="opacity: 0;"><img data-src="http://i1.ytimg.com/vi/oO9gU3pz7dI/hqdefault.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" /><div class="sqs-video-opaque"></div><div class="sqs-video-icon"></d